column5: My 2nd time out and finally caught my first musky of 2010.I was trolling with a 8" perch Believer,hooks were in good and had to cut them off. A 49 incher
First one of the season is 49"?  You've set the bar rather high right out of the gate dont you think?? LOL.  Great catch...an amazing fish!
Nice!!!!!  Still looking for my first, but, have only been out twice as well, hopefully third time is the charm. Starting with a 49", you "gotta" love it!!!!
That is a great fish. Those shots are neat. You can tell by the size of the head and shoulders that she is very healthy.  Congratulations; now you got to get her big sister.....  Tom.
zoinks...beauty fish. At least you have a few months left to try and beat it (good luck with that!)
Congrats! Nice looking fish....looks like a St Lawrence fish. Go get a bigger one!
Nice one...Is that a Metric 49?.....
Nice fish, great release shots!
Congrats, nice fish and great shots.  Really shows the head nice!!  Joey
Awesome fish for sure congratz heres to many more fatties this season
Nice Ski    Congrats
grats dude. gorgeous fish.
thx Going back saturday morning.
Awesome pics!  Nice fat fish.
Got a 44" on a black and orange topraider today.
Beauty PAIR of Musky for you now . . . you don't catch them small do you?  Those two are gorgeous and seeing reports like this makes me want to go and buy a musky setup!  Thanks for Sharing, Ryan
Very nice. You should have took one with you holding it up!
Congrats chong.my first was in pigeon lake1986/87. 1/2 less than the keeper limit.I still remember it to a tee to this day. Congrats man
I wanted to but with the heat wave here in Montreal I didn't want to take a chance of the fish dying.
Sweet ski
